## üîß Step-by-Step Setup

### 1. Set Up Google Cloud Speech-to-Text

#### a. Create a GCP Project

- Visit [Google Cloud Console](https://console.cloud.google.com/)
- Create a new project or select an existing one

#### b. Enable Billing

- Attach a billing account to your project

#### c. Enable the Speech-to-Text API

- Go to **APIs & Services ‚Üí Library**
- Search for ‚ÄúSpeech-to-Text API‚Äù and click **Enable**

#### d. Create a Service Account

- Navigate to **IAM & Admin ‚Üí Service Accounts**
- Click **Create Service Account**
- Assign the role: `Editor` or a custom role with Speech-to-Text permissions
- Generate a **JSON key** and download it securely

---

### 2. Configure Genesys Cloud Integration

#### a. Install the Integration

- Log in to [Genesys Cloud Admin](https://apps.mypurecloud.com/)
- Go to **Admin ‚Üí Integrations**
- Search for ‚ÄúGoogle Cloud Speech-to-Text‚Äù in AppFoundry
- Click **Install**

#### b. Upload Google Credentials

- During integration setup, upload the **JSON key file**
- This allows Genesys to authenticate with Google‚Äôs API

#### c. Configure Language and Audio Settings

- Choose a supported language (e.g., `en-IN` for Indian English)
- Set audio sampling rate (e.g., 8000 Hz for telephony)
- Optionally enable **Speech Adaptation** for custom phrases

---

### 3. Use in Architect Flows

#### a. Open Architect

- Go to **Admin ‚Üí Architect**
- Select or create a **Bot Flow** or **Inbound Call Flow**

#### b. Add Speech-to-Text Action

- Insert a **Speech Recognition** or **Bot Input** action
- Select the Google STT integration
- Map the audio input to a variable
- Use the transcribed text in decision logic or bot intents

---

### 4. Test and Validate

- Deploy a test flow with voice input
- Use real-world audio samples to validate transcription
- Monitor logs in Genesys and Google Cloud Console

